description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Reception/Administration Staff Emergency Services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Part Time: 18 hours,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Shift pattern: 1800-2300 this will include weekdays, weekends and nights.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a friendly, motivated and highly organised person with good I.T. skills and a flexible approach to join the team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be first point of contact for patients, visitors and other Health care Professionals, and will receive them in a professional and courteous manor.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The duties consist of patient registration on our Patient Centre IT program (full training will be given). Other duties include filing, and faxing, scanning, appointment booking and working as part of a team, which supports the Emergency Services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; Previous experience is desirable but not essential although sound overall administration &amp; IT skills are required along with a positive and enthusiastic approach.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You are required to have excellent Customer Service skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will need to be highly motivated team player, who shows flexibility and careful attention to detail providing patients with a high quality service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We pride ourselves on being a friendly positive team who are customer care focused and work closely together under pressure. If you like a fast paced atmosphere then we would love to hear from you. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Emergency Services consists of A/E UTC. This post is predominantly based in our Emergency Department but flexibility would be required for other areas within the Emergency Services. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
